Espa&#241;ola</i>, <i>AHE</i>), information provided by the Spanish authorities. 
<b>14
</b></p>
<p>  The Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD) has also expressed a 
similar concern: &#8220;Despite some signs of a property market slowdown, residential investment has 
reached 9.2 per cent of GDP, real estate prices are still rising about 10 per cent per year and 
household mortgage borrowing is growing excessively&#8221; (OECD Policy Brief, Economic Survey 
of Spain, January 2007). 
<b>15
</b></p>
